{
  "question_text": "<h3>Design Tic-Tac-Toe</h3><p>Verify if a player has won after each move on an $n \\times n$ board.</p>",
  "difficulty": "MEDIUM",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "Board size $n$, then moves (row, col, player).",
  "output_format": "Int winner (0 if none).",
  "constraints": [
    "n <= 100",
    "moves <= n^2"
  ],
  "explanation": "Store running counts for each row, column, and two diagonals for each player. A player wins if any count equals $n$.",
  "answer": "class TicTacToe:\n    def __init__(self, n):\n        self.n = n\n        self.rows = [0]*n; self.cols = [0]*n; self.diag = self.anti = 0\n    def move(self, r, c, p):\n        val = 1 if p == 1 else -1\n        self.rows[r] += val; self.cols[c] += val\n        if r == c: self.diag += val\n        if r + c == self.n - 1: self.anti += val\n        if any(abs(x) == self.n for x in [self.rows[r], self.cols[c], self.diag, self.anti]): return p\n        return 0",
